title: Point Reyes National Seashore: Media Quality Photos
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Photos & Multimedia     Photo Gallery     Media Quality Photos                Media Quality Photo Gallery       Compelling photography has contributed to the creation of the National Park Service and the preservation of America's most special places since artists first began capturing images of Yosemite and Yellowstone in the mid-1800s. Explore this gallery to find high-resolution images that represent the unique character of Point Reyes National Seashore and the work we do to protect Point Reyes for the next generation of park visitors, supporters, and advocates. To view media quality images from other National Park Service sites, visit the NPS Centennial Media-Quality Photo Gallery.   Â                 Media Quality Photo Gallery   10 Photos  Compelling photography has contributed to the creation of the National Park Service and the preservation of America's most special places since artists first began capturing images of Yosemite and Yellowstone in the mid-1800s. Explore this gallery to find high-resolution images that represent the unique character of Point Reyes National Seashore and the work the National Park Service does to protect them for the next generation of park visitors, supporters, and advocates. This gallery contains high quality images of at least 3,000 pixels on one side and at least 2 MB in size. Photographs credited to NPS without any copyright symbol are public domain. Photographs credited with a copyright symbol (indicating that the creator may maintain rights to the work) or credited to any entity other than NPS must not be presumed to be public domain; contact the host park or program to ascertain who owns the material.
